This paper proposes a measure of clustering quality that is appropriate for evaluating clustering algorithms in situations where there is confidence in the "ground truth" classes assigned to the patterns. This suggests that the paper is likely to be related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), or social and information networks (cs.SI), as these sub-categories often deal with clustering and classification tasks.
